misconceptions.inferred_category_name: No bug / correct right-rotation mental model
misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that to shift an array right by one with wraparound, you must (1) save the last element, (2) copy each element from left neighbor moving from right to left, then (3) put the saved last element into index 0.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: No conceptual gap detected: this matches Java’s actual execution model for array assignment. Iterating from N-1 down to 1 avoids overwriting values before they’re copied, and saving arr_nums[N-1] preserves the wraparound value.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: None (produces correct output for N>0, and correctly handles N=0 by doing nothing).
